<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
<taxonomicName LSID="370D9B13-4319-53B6-8E36-82193717402B" authority="Balf. f." authorityName="Balf. f." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Clerodendrum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clerodendrum thomsoniae" order="Lamiales" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thomsoniae">Clerodendrum thomsoniae Balf.f.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="names">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Names.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Myanmar</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">tike-pan</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">taik-pan-gyi</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">English</emphasis>
: bag-flower, bleeding-heart vine, glory tree, tropical bleeding heart.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="range">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">West and West-Central tropical Africa. Cultivated in Myanmar.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="uses">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Uses.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
Plant used for medicinal purposes (exact uses not given in 
<bibRefCitation author="Nordal, A" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="174" pageNumber="175" refId="B85" refString="Nordal, A, 1963. The Medicinal Plants and Crude Drugs of Burma. Hellstrom &amp; Nordahls Boktrykkeri, Oslo." title="The Medicinal Plants and Crude Drugs of Burma. Hellstrom &amp; Nordahls Boktrykkeri, Oslo." year="1963">Nordal 1963</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="95" lastPageNumber="96" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
Other members of the genus are reported as used medicinally in India, China, Thailand, Korea, and Japan for the treatment of such diseases as syphilis, typhoid, cancer, jaundice, and hypertension (
<bibRefCitation author="Shrivastava, N" journalOrPublisher="Medicinal and Aromatic Plant Science and Biotechnology" pageId="174" pageNumber="175" pagination="142 - 150" publicationUrl="http://www.globalsciencebooks.info/Online/GSBOnline/images/0706/MAPSB_1(1)/MAPSB_1(1)142-150o.pdf" refId="B104" refString="Shrivastava, N, Patel, T, 2007. Clerodendrum and healthcare: An overview. Medicinal and Aromatic Plant Science and Biotechnology 1: 142 - 150, http://www.globalsciencebooks.info/Online/GSBOnline/images/0706/MAPSB_1(1)/MAPSB_1(1)142-150o.pdf" title="Clerodendrum and healthcare: An overview." url="http://www.globalsciencebooks.info/Online/GSBOnline/images/0706/MAPSB_1(1)/MAPSB_1(1)142-150o.pdf" volume="1" year="2007">Shrivastava and Patel 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
<pageBreakToken pageId="95" pageNumber="96" start="start">Major</pageBreakToken>
chemical compounds have been reported from this genus. These include phenolics, steroids, di- and tri-terpenes, flavonoids, volatile oils, etc. (
<bibRefCitation author="Shrivastava, N" journalOrPublisher="Medicinal and Aromatic Plant Science and Biotechnology" pageId="174" pageNumber="175" pagination="142 - 150" publicationUrl="http://www.globalsciencebooks.info/Online/GSBOnline/images/0706/MAPSB_1(1)/MAPSB_1(1)142-150o.pdf" refId="B104" refString="Shrivastava, N, Patel, T, 2007. Clerodendrum and healthcare: An overview. Medicinal and Aromatic Plant Science and Biotechnology 1: 142 - 150, http://www.globalsciencebooks.info/Online/GSBOnline/images/0706/MAPSB_1(1)/MAPSB_1(1)142-150o.pdf" title="Clerodendrum and healthcare: An overview." url="http://www.globalsciencebooks.info/Online/GSBOnline/images/0706/MAPSB_1(1)/MAPSB_1(1)142-150o.pdf" volume="1" year="2007">Shrivastava and Patel 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
